# Documentation Standards

## Integration Types
| Type | When to Use |
|------|-------------|
| Code | Users install Opik Python SDK, use `track_*()` wrappers |
| LiteLLM | LLM provider via OpikLogger callback |
| OpenTelemetry | Config-only via OTEL env vars, NO SDK features |

**Critical:** OTEL integrations NEVER include `@track`, evaluation, or `opik.configure()`.

## Page Frontmatter
```yaml
title: Observability for [Name] with Opik
description: Start here to integrate Opik into your [NAME]-based app...
```
- Include language spec `(Python)` in title ONLY when multiple language versions exist
- Navigation and overview cards: NO language specs (context from section)

## Integration Docs
Location: `apps/opik-documentation/documentation/fern/docs/tracing/integrations/`
Navigation: `docs.yml` under `integrations` tab, organized by language

## When Adding Integrations
Update ALL of:
1. README.md (and translations: readme_CN/JP/KO.md)
2. `docs/tracing/integrations/overview.mdx`
3. `docs.yml` navigation
4. Integration page itself

## Cursor Rules
Place in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` with kebab-case names. Use frontmatter: `description`, `globs`, `alwaysApply`.
